sample_description: Protocols: Patients were recruited from malaria endemic areas in Thailand (Ubon Ratchathani and Yala). Patients were confirmed infected with P. vivax through microscopic examination and molecular approach. Blood specimen was preserved in RNALater until processed.  Five hundred micro litre of each blood specimen preserved in RNALater® was processed individually using a QIAamp RNA blood mini kit. RNA samples were treated with DNase, followed by Epicentre Globin-Zero Gold kit to deplete rRNA and globin transcript. RNA-seq libraries were prepared using the NEBNext Ultra Directional protocol.
